description: Dark Reign strikes Marvel’s first family—in an explosive way! Prepared to be blown away as: HAMMER agents attack the Baxter Building. Reed changes everything. The Human Torch suffers a horrible loss and Franklin and Val go shopping. There's Time travel, Alternate realities, Celestials, Eternals, Deviants and Doombots... and more important than all of that, we find out the answer to the question: What is the Bridge?

description:
One of the first comics to appear with original material in it this was the only issue of Detective Dan to appear, the company that put it out, Humor Publications Co., then went out of business after publishing only three tabloid sized comics.

Dan Dunn the star however would move over to Dell, as well as being picked up by a syndicate that put him in newspapers, he also would show up in a pulp magazine (2 issues) and a radio show (57 episodes.)

Then he would disappear.
name: Detective Dan Secret Op. 48.
Guns And Roses, Chapter 3 - Hang' Em High!

name: Issue 1
The Girl Who Came in From the Cold

description:
The third chapter of the RoboCop films explodes onto the comics page! OCP -- the company responsible for Officer Murphy's transformation into RoboCop -- is planning to build a grand new community of the future on the ashes of Old Detroit, and perhaps a few of its current residents as well!

When a gang of criminals calling themselves Splatterpunks start making things difficult for the OCP developers, RoboCop finds himself drawn into the struggle. Will RoboCop follow the orders of the OCP and drive the defenseless citizens of Detroit from their homes? Don't count on it! With the help of Nikko, a young computer genius, RoboCop takes on the forces of OCP in an inner-city battle to the death!
name: Issue 1

description: Reprints Amazing Spider-Man #186-210, Amazing Spider-Man Annual #13-14, and Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual #1.
name: Volume 9

description: It's a sad day in Delta City when Officer Lewis, RoboCop's trusted friend and longtime partner, is shot by OCP's hired goons. Framed for the murder, the badly damaged cyborg is taken in by the Delta City underground, the very organization he was commanded to stop. Surrounded by uneasy allies and traitors, RoboCop sets out to avenge Anne Lewis and save the innocent citizens of Detroit from the corporation that created him.
name: Issue 2

description: The explosive conclusion to the comic adaptation of the hit film! RoboCop and the Detroit Police take a stand against the terrorist tactics of OCP and their Rehab officers, to help the innocent victims of Delta City save their homes. It's a heavy-metal showdown in the streets -- and in the OCP boardroom -- riddled with suspense, action, intrigue, and plenty of firepower! Don't miss it!
name: Issue 3

description: Hot on the heels of the recent Dark Horse Comics "RoboCop: Invasions" story, this new four-issue series, brought to you by the same creative team of Grant, Gnazzo, and Patterson, gets off to a chilly start in the snow-covered environs of a strangely desolate Colorado. RoboCop and Marie Lazarus are looking for Coffin, implicated in the recent OCP break-in, and follow an FBI lead to Denver in search of the huge hatchet man. But before they get to delve into the reasons for Coffin being in Denver, they have to deal with Hooks and his band of high-tech highway scavengers!

Detroit's no longer big enough to hold newly appointed Federal Marshall RoboCop, as he and Dr. Marie Lazarus travel to Colorado to track down Coffin. Multi-billionaire Edward Agincourt runs Denver with an iron fist and a big gun, and Coffin, his right-hand man, is loaded for bear -- and out for RoboCop's blood! Add a bunch of bilious bikers scavenging for spare parts, a dollop of local townsfolk with misplaced loyalties, and a pinch of police deputies-for-hire into the mix, and you've got the recipe for some slam-bang excitement!

With RoboCop seemingly at the mercy of Coffin, Hooks and his band of scavengers ride to his rescue at the last minute -- but is it to save RoboCop's neck, or just Hooks' self-interest in a potentially lucrative salvage operation? Meanwhile, Marie Lazarus is a reluctant guest at Edward Agincourt's palatial Denver estate. Agincourt mysteriously hints that very soon time will no longer be of concern to him... but what on earth does this have to do with Dr. Lazarus? Or RoboCop, for that matter?

Edward Agincourt has one last trick left up his sleeve before he leaves this mortal earth, and Marie has been drafted against her will to help him accomplish his goal. Meanwhile, RoboCop and Hooks have found they have a set of common enemies in Agincourt and his henchman, Coffin, and set out to rid Denver of them once and for all.

By Wilfred Santiago; the creator of The Thorn Garden returns with three new erotic stories guaranteed to take you to the limits of fantasy -- and beyond! From a barrio where horny teens embark on a sex-fuelled journey of nihilistic hedonism, to a sharp satire of the world of supermodels (starring two depraved twin sisters who moonlight as private detectives), to a desperate young slut carving out a living in a kinky third-world society, these stories view the world through a thick wash of bodily fluids that'll leave you seeing Pink.

Amidst a deadly blizzard, he must find an ancient monument and unlock its secrets before someone with much darker intentions gets there first! Yet there are trials awaiting any who would lay claim to the artifacts of mysterious warriors from long ago.
